-- DuluxGroup Hires Westpac for A$270 Million Alesco Buyout Loan
-- B y   K a t r i n a   N i c h o l a s
-- 2012-05-02T01:14:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-02/duluxgroup-hires-westpac-for-a-270-million-alesco-buyout-loan.html
DuluxGroup Ltd. (DLX) , a maker and supplier
of paints and other surface coatings, hired  Westpac Banking
Corp. (WBC)  to help organize a A$270 million loan, according to an e-
mailed statement.  Proceeds will be used to finance DuluxGroup’s all-cash
offer to acquire the shares it doesn’t already own in Alesco
Corp., an Australian garage door maker.  The loan will be split into a A$220 million three-year
revolving credit facility and a A$50 million 18-month bridge
facility, according to the statement. Westpac is marketing the
A$220 million facility to other banks in syndication.  DuluxGroup’s brands include Dulux, Selleys, British Paints
and Dynamic Lifter.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Katrina Nicholas at 
 knicholas2@bloomberg.net  